# Generated architecture artifacts must check out as LF on every platform.
#
# tools/gen-repo-map.js, gen-symbols.js and gen-specs-index.js each support a
# --check mode that CI runs as the "Generated Artifacts In Sync" job. That check
# is a strict byte comparison between the file on disk and freshly generated
# output, and the generators emit LF (JSON.stringify / template literals).
#
# On Windows, core.autocrlf=true checks these files out as CRLF, so the byte
# comparison fails and all three report "stale" even when their content is
# identical -- regenerating produces no diff. Pinning them to LF makes the
# working tree, the stored blob and the generator output agree everywhere.
#
# Deliberately NOT solved by normalising line endings inside the --check
# comparison: that would also mask a genuine EOL discrepancy in a committed
# artifact. Better for the files to be incapable of drifting.
specs/_architecture_/repo-map.json text eol=lf
specs/_architecture_/symbols.json  text eol=lf
specs/INDEX.md                     text eol=lf
